metadata.description:
This <Unfavorable tanshiro 100> will be the final release of this series. 

Unfavorable Tanshiro is a p5.js generative character made by @tanshiro1986.
Everyday I draw a new factor, and post a unique Tanshiro on twitter. 

Today is the 100th day since Tanshiro's birth.
Unfavorable Tanshiro #1~#99 were released on Opensea as daily record, and this memorable #100 will be concluded, improved, and released on fx(hash).

There are 1000 unique Tashiro coming from 2,400,000 different combinations.
Some special factors are the collab with JT's artwork.

metadata.name: Sea of Shapes #73
metadata.description:
This program was inspired by the 2022 Genuary prompt "Make a sea of shapes." It is an abstract and geometric representation of water and waves. I tried to capture the many different possible states of a sea (windy, breezy, calm etc.) by changing parameters within the program for different outputs.

Press 'p' while on Live View to save a high quality (4000x4000) png of the canvas.

Created using p5.js

metadata.name: Letter #287
metadata.description:
This is a letter from the computer to you by asemic writing. Imagine what message is written on it.

The artwork is inspired from Shodo(書道) that is known as Japanese calligraphy.
Shodo is the way of writing Kanji and Kana characters with a brush in India ink.
It's one of the traditional Japanese arts.

Paper Color and Ink Color combinations has 18 variations.
Aspect Ratio has 5 variations.
Font Size has 3 variations.
Font Weight has 3 variations.
Font Style has 3 variations.
Each character is randomly generated by a mathematical algorithm.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [f] to switch full screen on and off
- Press [s] to download a PNG file with windowsize
- Press [l] to download a PNG file with large size 4800 pixel  (wait a minutes)

Create with p5.js
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Rearranged #65
metadata.description:
Rearranged is an invitation to engage in an exploration of aesthetics within the constraints of the generated token. 

Each piece has 4 layers. Each layer can be independently rotated by 90 degrees clockwise by clicking 1,2,3 or 4 on the keyboard. Some changes are subtle. Some are surprising. 

's' on the keyboard will scramble all of the rotations.
'r' will reset to the original artwork.

You are invited to: 
arrange a more aesthetically pleasing piece than the original;
scramble the artwork and use the number keys to return it to its original state;
work out which shapes have been erased from each layer.

And of course there is also a gorgeous gradient illusion made of solid-colour filled tessellating shapes. 

3 tessellations of varying sizes, 12 layouts with random elements, 14 palettes.

Made with p5.js.
